      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0600P0-03817'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0600P0_19990510_GCR_244' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Lord Dixon-Smith</span> had given notice of his intention to move Amendment No.37:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0600P0-03818'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0600P0_19990510_GCR_245' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Page 4, line 10, leave out paragraphs (a) and (b)
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0600P0-03819'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0600P0_19990510_GCR_246' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Lord said: This amendment follows on from the previous one. If the previous amendment were accepted, then this would become necessary to make sense of what is written there. It is in that sense that it was advanced.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0600P0-03820'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0600P0_19990510_GCR_247' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        [<span class="italic">Amendment No.37 not moved</span>.]
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0600P0-03821'>
